----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.Styles
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the font styles of the items in the label.
Description
  Use Styles to access the font styles used on individual items in the label. Index must be between 0
  and Lines.Count - 1.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.SetStyle, TJvInstallLabel.SetExclusive, TJvInstallLabel.SetImage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.TextOffset
Summary
  Specifies how far from the left edge the text is displayed on the label.
Description
  Use TextOffset to set the number of pixels from the left edge items are drawn.
  Note
  Setting ImageOffset to a high value and TextOffset to a low value might result in images and texts
  overlapping.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.ImageOffset, TJvInstallLabel.Lines, TJvInstallLabel.LineSpacing

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.SetImage
Summary
  Changes the image for a single item.
Description
  Call SetImage to change the image displayed to the left of an item.
Parameters
  LineIndex  - Index of the item to change.
  ImageIndex - The new image index for the item.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.SetExclusive, TJvInstallLabel.SetStyle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.SetStyle
Summary
  Changes the font style and image for a single item.
Description
  Call SetStyle to change the visual appearance of a single item. All other items are unaffected.
Parameters
  LineIndex  - Index of the item to change.
  ImageIndex - The new image index for the item.
  LineStyle  - The new font style for the item.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.SetImage, TJvInstallLabel.SetExclusive

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.SetExclusive
Summary
  Changes all items back to default setting except for one item.
Description
  Use SetExclusive when you want to make an item exclusive in the label. All other items will be
  reset to the default settings, resetting font style to that of the label and the image to
  DefaultImage.
Parameters
  LineIndex  - Index of the item to make exclusive.
  ImageIndex - Index of the image to display.
  LineStyle  - \Font style for the exclusive item.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.SetImage, TJvInstallLabel.SetStyle

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.LineSpacing
Summary
  Specifies the horizontal distance between text lines in the label.
Description
  Use LineSpacing to set the amount of space between the text lines in the label. LineSpacing is
  expressed in pixels.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.ImageOffset, TJvInstallLabel.Lines, TJvInstallLabel.TextOffset

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.Lines
Summary
  The text strings that are displayed on the label.
Description
  Lines is of type TStrings and each item in Lines is displayed on a separate line in the label along
  with an optional image. Use the methods of TStrings (Add, \Delete, Assign etc) to change the
  content of the label.
See Also
  <DELPHILINK TStrings>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.Images
Summary
  Lists images available for the items in the label.
Description
  Images is a list of bitmaps that can be displayed to the left of any item in the label. Each item
  can specify an image from this list by using the <LINK TJvInstallLabel.SetImage, SetImage> routine.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.SetImage

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.ImageOffset
Summary
  Specifies the amount of space to the left of each item image.
Description
  Use ImageOffset to set the number of pixels from the left edge that images are drawn.
  Note
  Setting ImageOffset to a high value and TextOffset to a low value might result in images and texts
  overlapping.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.LineSpacing, TJvInstallLabel.TextOffset

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallLabel.DefaultImage
Summary
  Specifies the image to use for new items.
Description
  Use DefaultImage to set the image to use for items that have not yet explicitly been assigned an
  ImageIndex. DefaultImage should be set to a value that corresponds to the index of the image in
  Images. To not display any image for the items, set DefaultImage to -1.
See Also
  TJvInstallLabel.Images

